## Phase 1: Project Restructure & Replit Cleanup

> **Goal:** Clean folder structure, remove Replit, project runs independently

| # | Task | Details | Source Code |
|---|------|---------|-------------|
| 1.1 | Create clean folder structure | `client/` from `artifacts/global-college/`, `server/` from `artifacts/api-server/`, `db/` from `lib/db/` | Copy existing code |
| 1.2 | Delete Replit files | `.replit`, `.replitignore`, `replit.md`, `.agents/`, `.local/`, `artifacts/mockup-sandbox/` | Delete |
| 1.3 | Clean `pnpm-workspace.yaml` | Remove all `@replit/*` exclusions, linux-only overrides, Replit comments | Edit existing |
| 1.4 | Fix `vite.config.ts` | Remove `@replit/vite-plugin-*` (3 plugins), `REPL_ID` checks, make PORT/BASE_PATH optional with defaults | Edit existing |
| 1.5 | Fix `package.json` files | Remove `@replit/*` from devDeps, update workspace references | Edit existing |
| 1.6 | Create `.env.example` | All env vars: DATABASE_URL, JWT_SECRET, PORT, etc. | Create new |
| 1.7 | Create root `package.json` scripts | `dev`, `build`, `db:migrate`, `db:push`, `db:studio` | Edit existing |
| 1.8 | Verify project runs | `pnpm install` → `pnpm dev` should start both client and server | Test |

**Checkpoint:** ✅ Project starts independently without Replit

---

## Phase 2: Authentication & Security Foundation

> **Goal:** Proper JWT auth, bcrypt, RBAC middleware — replace in-memory sessions

| # | Task | Details | Source Code |
|---|------|---------|-------------|
| 2.1 | Install auth dependencies | `bcryptjs`, `jsonwebtoken`, `@types/bcryptjs`, `@types/jsonwebtoken` | New packages |
| 2.2 | Replace SHA-256 with bcrypt | `hashPassword()` → `bcrypt.hash(pw, 12)`, `verifyPassword()` → `bcrypt.compare()` | Rewrite `lib/auth.ts` |
| 2.3 | Implement JWT token system | Access token (7-day), refresh token (30-day), token signing/verification | Rewrite `lib/auth.ts` |
| 2.4 | Build `authenticate` middleware | Verify JWT from `Authorization: Bearer` header, attach `req.user` | New file |
| 2.5 | Build `authorize(roles)` middleware | Check `req.user.role` against allowed roles array | New file |
| 2.6 | Build global error handler | `AppError` class + `errorHandler` middleware | New files |
| 2.7 | Build `catchAsync` utility | Wraps async route handlers, catches errors | New file |
| 2.8 | Rebuild login endpoint | Use bcrypt verify, return JWT tokens, handle account lock | Rewrite `routes/auth.ts` |
| 2.9 | Rebuild register endpoint | Hash with bcrypt, validate inputs, return JWT | Rewrite `routes/auth.ts` |
| 2.10 | Build `/auth/me` endpoint | Decode JWT, return user without sensitive fields | Rewrite |
| 2.11 | Build `/auth/refresh` endpoint | Validate refresh token, issue new access token | New endpoint |
| 2.12 | Update frontend AuthContext | Store JWT tokens, add to all API requests via interceptor | Edit `AuthContext.tsx` |

**Checkpoint:** ✅ Login/Register works with JWT + bcrypt, routes are protected

---

## Phase 3: Database Schema Completion

> **Goal:** All tables match PRD requirements with proper relationships

| # | Task | Details |
|---|------|---------|
| 3.1 | Update `users` table | Add: `branchId` (FK), `isEmailVerified`, `isIdentityVerified`, `failedLoginAttempts`, `lockedUntil`, `profilePhoto` |
| 3.2 | Update `courses` table | Add: `slug` (unique), `status` enum, `rejectionNote`, `totalDurationHours` |
| 3.3 | Create `sections` table | New: `id`, `courseId` (FK), `title`, `order` |
| 3.4 | Update `lessons` table | Add: `sectionId` (FK), `encryptedYoutubeId`, `completionThreshold`. Remove `videoUrl` |
| 3.5 | Create `lessonCompletions` table | Replace `lessonProgress`: add `watchedPercent`, `lastPositionSeconds`, `isCompleted`, `completedAt` |
| 3.6 | Create `videoAccessLogs` table | New: `userId`, `lessonId`, `ipAddress`, `userAgent`, `accessedAt` |
| 3.7 | Normalize `quizzes` schema | Separate `questions` table with: `questionText`, `optionA-D`, `correctOption`, `explanation`, `order` |
| 3.8 | Update `payments` table | Add: `rejectionReason`, `reviewedAt`, `reviewedBy` |
| 3.9 | Update `certificates` table | Add: `pdfUrl`, `status`, `isRevoked` |
| 3.10 | Add unique constraints & indexes | Enrollment(userId+courseId), LessonCompletion(userId+lessonId), Course(slug), etc. |

**Checkpoint:** ✅ `pnpm db:push` runs successfully, all tables created

---

## Phase 4: Core API Infrastructure

> **Goal:** Standard API patterns, validation, pagination ready for all routes

| # | Task | Details |
|---|------|---------|
| 4.1 | Create standard response helpers | `sendSuccess(res, data, msg)`, `sendError(res, code, msg)` → consistent `{success, data, message}` format |
| 4.2 | Create validation middleware | `validate(schema)` middleware using Zod schemas |
| 4.3 | Create pagination utility | `paginate(query, page, limit)` → returns `{data, total, page, totalPages}` |
| 4.4 | Add API versioning | Mount all routes under `/api/v1/` |
| 4.5 | Create file upload middleware | Multer config for images/PDFs/docs with MIME validation |
| 4.6 | Setup Cloudinary service | Upload/delete helpers for images, PDFs, receipts |
| 4.7 | Create logger service | Winston logger with levels: error, warn, info, debug |
| 4.8 | Add rate limiting | `express-rate-limit` on auth routes |
| 4.9 | Add security middleware | `helmet()`, `cors()` with proper config, `xss-clean` |

**Checkpoint:** ✅ API infrastructure ready, all middleware working

